Here I thought it was short for gigolo.  <img src=3D"https://cdn.jsdelivr.n=
et/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f600.png" class=3D"smilie smilie--e=
moji" loading=3D"lazy" width=3D"64" height=3D"64" alt=3D":D" title=3D"Big G=
rin    :D" data-smilie=3D"8" data-shortname=3D":D"><br>
<br>
Seriously, it's not all garbage, just some of it is.  Elo says Djokovic and=
 Federer have the highest hardcourt peaks, and Nadal and Borg have the high=
est clay peaks.  I agree with both of these.  However, it also says Borg an=
d Laver have the highest grass peaks and Connors has a higher grass peak th=
an Sampras, putting him at #7 and Federer at #3.  I completely disagree wit=
h this but this is its major flaw because in a short season like grass, it =
can't distinguish the enormous difference between Wimbledon and smaller gra=
ss tournaments, rating them the same and the genius of Sampras and Federer =
is not measured correctly.</div>
