	</div>
</blockquote>ELO tells you how tough was the opposition player faced in a l=
imited timeframe. It's great as additional information while evaluating ATG=
 achievements. <br>
For instance, in RG2015-RG2016 one year period, Novak Djokovic accumulated =
most ATP points in tennis history. Critic might say he was lucky to play ag=
ainst weaker players during tournaments, that his opposition was weaker tha=
n overall competition. Here is where ELO jumps in to tell us if it's true, =
because it measures exactly that - opposition level. In that 2015-2016 time=
frame, Novak achieved historic ELO record (highest ever) together with hist=
oric ATP points record (highest ever). This helps us recognize he played ag=
ainst very strong / strongest opposition while winning more than anybody el=
se, confirming his BOAT status.</div>
