k=3D"attribution" data-content-selector=3D"#post-16291345">LuckyR said:</a>
		=09
		</div>
=09
	<div class=3D"bbCodeBlock-content">
	=09
		<div class=3D"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			The problem with using win vs loss as a measure in tennis is the 2 out o=
f three set nature of the competition. It means that if a player has 50% of=
 the skill level they will win zero % of matches (not 25%). Also 6-0, 6-0 w=
ins are treated the same as 0-6, 7-6, 7-6 wins which would be the differenc=
e between me playing Rafa and Alcaraz<br>
playing him.<br>
<br>
Basing ratings on games won, rather than matches won would broaden the skil=
l levels where results would be accurate (and therefore helpful).
		</div>
		<div class=3D"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role=3D"button" ta=
bindex=3D"0">Click to expand...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>WINNING a match IS what counts, not the score.</div>
