		=09

			<div itemprop=3D"text">
			=09
					<div class=3D"bbWrapper">It's a fine rating system. Nothing wrong with=
 it, but don't expect miracles out of it either.<br>
<br>
It's reasonably accurate when comparing a player against their immediate op=
ponents. I'd certainly trust it more than the ATP ranking for predicting wh=
o's going to win a first-round match, especially between players outside th=
e top 32 who are often unseeded and whose ATP ranking is going to be heavil=
y affected by just a few tournaments where they got a good draw. I doubt it=
's particularly good for predicting who's gonna win a grand slam final, but=
 then again ATP rating isn't that great for that either in cases where it's=
 not obvious, so the bar's low, maybe Elo's ok for that too.<br>
<br>
Trying to use it to compare eras, or trying to compare something like "peak=
 ELO" to see who's "greater" is pointless.</div>
